<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 12:15PM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Randolph, Lawrence
and southeastern Sharp Counties through 100 PM CDT...
At 1215 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from Dalton to Ravenden to 6 miles northeast of Cave
City. Movement was east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Pocahontas...                     Walnut Ridge...
Hoxie...                          Black Rock...
Lake Charles State Park...        Imboden...
Ravenden...                       Reyno...
College City...                   Portia...
Maynard...                        Biggers...
Lynn...                           O`Kean...
Ravenden Springs...               Minturn...
Annieville...                     Dalton...
Attica...                         Sedgwick...
This includes US Highway 67 between mile markers 115 and 121.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
